</span>
</span></p><h2>How to Make Mashed Sweet Potatoes</h2><p>Like in my <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/mashed-cauliflower-recipe/ >mashed cauliflower recipe</a>, I don&#8217;t actually mash the sweet potatoes here. Instead, I puree them in a food processor to create a super smooth, creamy texture. If you prefer to use a potato masher to achieve a chunkier texture, feel free, but I adore this method:</p><p><strong>First, bake the potatoes</strong>. When I make <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/mashed-potatoes/ >traditional mashed potatoes</a>, I start by boiling the potatoes. But when I&#8217;m working with sweet potatoes, I <a
href=https://www.loveandlemons.com/baked-sweet-potato/ >bake them</a>. It concentrates their sweet flavor and makes their flesh smooth and creamy&#8230;perfect for mashed sweet potatoes! Wash the potatoes, and poke a few holes in them with a fork. Place them on a foil-lined baking sheet and bake at 425° for 60 minutes, or until tender. You should be able to easily pierce them with a fork.</p><p>
<span
class="pibfi_pinterest ">
<img
class="alignnone wp-image-52774 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0naHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmcnIHdpZHRoPScxMTYwJyBoZWlnaHQ9JzE0NjUnPjwvc3ZnPg==" data-original=https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/mashed-sweet-potato-recipes.jpg alt="Easy mashed sweet potatoes in a food processor" width=1160 height=1465 data-pin-description="These mashed sweet potatoes are SO creamy and delicious! Seasoned with garlic, ginger, and rosemary, they're an easy, healthy, and flavorful side dish. Perfect for the holidays! | Love and Lemons #thanksgiving #holidayrecipes #sweetpotatoes #sidedish" data-srcset="https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/mashed-sweet-potato-recipes.jpg 1160w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/mashed-sweet-potato-recipes-238x300.jpg 238w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/mashed-sweet-potato-recipes-811x1024.jpg 811w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/mashed-sweet-potato-recipes-79x100.jpg 79w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/mashed-sweet-potato-recipes-580x733.jpg 580w" sizes="(max-width: 1160px) 100vw, 1160px" data-pin-url=https://www.loveandlemons.com/mashed-sweet-potatoes/ >
<span
class=xc_pin onclick="pin_this(event, 'http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https://www.loveandlemons.com/mashed-sweet-potatoes/&media=https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/mashed-sweet-potato-recipes.jpg&description=These+mashed+sweet+potatoes+are+SO+creamy+and+delicious%21+Seasoned+with+garlic%2C+ginger%2C+and+rosemary%2C+they%27re+an+easy%2C+healthy%2C+and+flavorful+side+dish.+Perfect+for+the+holidays%21+%7C+Love+and+Lemons+%23thanksgiving+%23holidayrecipes+%23sweetpotatoes+%23sidedish')">
</span>
</span></p><p><strong>Next, blend!</strong> When the potatoes are cool enough to handle, peel away their skins. Transfer the cooked flesh to a food processor, along with the milk, butter or oil, rosemary, garlic, ginger, salt, and pepper. Process until creamy, and season to taste.</p><p><strong>Finally, eat.</strong> Serve the mashed sweet potatoes hot, topped with a sprinkle of thyme leaves, a pat of butter, and salt and pepper. Enjoy!</p><p>
